Cell["\<\
In January, 2025, there were 23 weekdays and 3 holidays: New Year\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s Day, Martin Luther King Jr. Day, and, for that year \
specifically, Jan. 9, when the markets were closed for the death of President \
Carter. The total number of daily closing prices should therefore be 20.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978833435031385*^9, 
  3.978833550888585*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f6cc617d-2867-4755-a4df-\
6f14035698a2"],

Cell["\<\
REMARK: Sometimes, for reasons beyond the ken of mortal men, the above call \
to FinancialData[] claims to return only 18 data points. If that happens, \
call FinancialData[] with different arguments, like FinancialData[\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]AAPL\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]], then try again. \
Wolfram, once again, knocks it out of the park on quality control.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9744361942082853`*^9, 3.974436225588442*^9}, {
  3.974458887676791*^9, 3.974458923032147*^9}, {3.9744677697928534`*^9, 
